MASTERS TOURNAMENT
April 8, 2009
Riley Moris
START_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT
 
 
  
 
  
  
   
  Q. Can you tell us, what was that like when you went out there?  
 RILEY MORIS: I was kind of nervous at first, and then I was excited for myself when I made it.  
  
  Q. What was it like when all of those people started yelling for you when you made the putt?  
 RILEY MORIS: I felt happy.  
  
  Q. Have you ever made a putt before is this?  
 RILEY MORIS: Mm-hmmm.  
  
  Q. How much golf do you play?  
 RILEY MORIS: Not much.   
  
  Q. Do you like it?  
 RILEY MORIS: Yes, sir.  
  
  Q. What do you like about it?   
 RILEY MORIS: Well, I like it because it's fun to watch people make holes.   
  
  Q. When Fuzzy Zoeller walked by, did you know who he was?  
 RILEY MORIS: Not really.  
  
  Q. What did you think when he said, come with me?   
 RILEY MORIS: I felt happy.   
  
  Q. Are you a golfer yourself?   
 RILEY MORIS: No, ma'am.   
   
  End of FastScripts  
  

